Description: Do not treat warnings as errors in the vendored Fast DDS build
 Fedora's build injects -Werror via CMAKE_CXX_FLAGS_INIT, which turns benign
 upstream warnings (unused-but-set variables in CacheChange.hpp, the bundled
 sqlite3 amalgamation, etc.) into hard errors on Fedora's GCC. Add
 add_compile_options(-Wno-error) (a directory option applied after
 CMAKE_CXX_FLAGS) so the vendored build is not gated on upstream's warning
 cleanliness. Upstream keeps -Werror only in its own CI.
Origin: vendor-specific
Forwarded: not-needed, downstream packaging relaxation of warnings-as-errors
Last-Update: 2026-06-03
--- a/CMakeLists.txt	2026-06-02 20:38:00.542123484 -0500
+++ b/CMakeLists.txt	2026-06-02 20:38:00.552157760 -0500
@@ -73,6 +73,9 @@
     # Add some generic warnings common to all compilers
     set(CMAKE_CXX_FLAGS
         "${CMAKE_CXX_FLAGS} -Wall -Wpedantic -Wextra -Wno-unknown-pragmas -Wno-error=deprecated-declarations -Wno-switch-bool")
+    # Fedora injects -Werror via CMAKE_CXX_FLAGS_INIT; relax it (downstream
+    # vendored build, not upstream CI) so unused-but-set warnings do not fail.
+    add_compile_options($<$<COMPILE_LANGUAGE:CXX>:-Wno-error>)
     # Add compiler specific options
     if(CMAKE_CXX_COMPILER_ID STREQUAL "GNU")
         set(CMAKE_CXX_FLAGS "${CMAKE_CXX_FLAGS} -Wno-psabi")
